President Cyril Ramaphosa. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to address the nation on Monday at 8pm on South Africa’s response to the COVID-19 pandemic. There are expectations that harsher restrictions will be announced. South Africa's confirmed COVID-19 infections surpassed 1 million. The Eastern Cape and Western Cape have recorded the most deaths. Catch the address live on eNCA DStv403 and eNCA.com